cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DC 

This paper is about using deep learning techniques to automatically reconstruct entire cells from volume electron microscopy data for brain mapping. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of distributed training, which falls under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The use of deep learning techniques also suggests that the paper could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper discusses the optimization of the training process, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
